[These data show that the outbreak peaked between weeks 20 and 25 and
declined to pre-outbreak levels by week 33. The outbreak in the
Madrid region now appears to be over. Of the total cases, 81 percent
were confirmed as viral infections (echovirus 30 and echovirus 6).
The same serotypes were associated also with viral meningitis
outbreaks in Latvia later in the summer -- see ProMED-mail post:
Meningitis - Latvia (Rezekne & Daugavpils) (02) 20061005.2850. - Mod.CP]
